esapi.unifreiburg.javadoc
Class JavaDocExample

java.lang.Object
  esapi.unifreiburg.javadoc.JavaDocExample

public class JavaDocExample
extends java.lang.Object

EsapiAuthorized class authorized user object which is stored inside user.txt file and Base on,User is able to visualized certain part of application.

For example :-
<esapi:authorization role="admin">
Admin Content.
<esapi:authorization>

As Content stored inside above Tag,is visible to user with Admin role only. and all sub component inside this will be rendered and content showed inside page. Moreover,admin could see data inside admin tag as well as data inside other tag but norman user can not see data inside admin tag because they don't have right's to see admin content.

For example :-
<esapi:authorization role="user">
User Content.
</esapi:authorization>

User with above role user could see only data, which is inside this tag but other important data with other roles is not visualized to them.

Method Detail

main

public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
Draws as much of the specified image as is currently available with its northwest corner at the specified coordinate (x, y). This method will return immediately in all cases, even if the entire image has not yet been scaled, dithered and converted for the current output device.

If the current output representation is not yet complete then the method will return false and the indicated ImageObserver object will be notified as the conversion process progresses.

Parameters:
img - the image to be drawn
x - the x-coordinate of the northwest corner of the destination rectangle in pixels
y - the y-coordinate of the northwest corner of the destination rectangle in pixels
observer - the image observer to be notified as more of the image is converted. May be null
Since:
1.0
See Also:
Image, ImageObserver
